    section
      h2 Form elements

      p Using forms in muffins default-theme is very easy. You can combine all standard forms and - of course - the grid. 
      p All form elements are styled based on their type attribute or a class. Here you get an short overview for what you con realize with the default-theme

      h6 Example
      .example
        form
          .row
            .col-xs-12
              label 
                | Input Label
                input type="text" placeholder=".col-xs-12"
          .row
            .col-xs-6
              label  
                | Input Label
                input type="text" placeholder=".col-xs-6"
            .col-xs-6
              .row.collapse
                label Input Label
                .col-xs-9
                  input type="text" placeholder=".col-xs-9"
                .col-xs-3
                  span.postfix .com
          .row
            .col-xs-12
              label  
                | Select Box
                select
                  option value="gingerbread" Gingerbread
                  option value="croissant" Croissant
                  option value="tiramisu" Tiramisu
                  option value="gummies" Gummies
          .row
            .col-xs-12
              label  Choose a color
              input type="radio" name="color" value="Red" id="colorRed"
              label for="colorRed" Red
              input type="radio" name="color" value="Blue" id="colorBlue"
              label for="colorBlue" Blue
            .col-xs-6
              label Choose one
              input id="checkbox1" type="checkbox"
              label for="checkbox1" Checkbox 1
              input id="checkbox2" type="checkbox"
              label for="checkbox2" Checkbox 2
          .row
            .col-xs-12
              label  
                | Textarea Label
                textarea placeholder="col-xs-12"

      section
        h3 Fieldset legend
        p 
          | A Fieldset is used as a wrapper right inside the form element. Right after you define a fieldset, you can include a legend title. You can easily adjust the formatting of the fieldset and legend by changing the following variables in 
          code config/_forms.scss
          | :
        p
          code $color-border-fieldset
          | Border color for the fieldset. (default: $color-brand-primary)
        p
          code $color-background-fieldset-legend
          | Background color for the legend in the fieldset. (default: $color-white)

        h6 Usage
        pre
          code
            header HTML
            p
              = '<form>'
              br
              = '  <fieldset>'
              br
              = '    <legend> Legend </legend>' 
              br
              = '    <label>Input label'
              br
              = '      <input type="text" placeholder="Input placeholder....">'
              br
              = '    </label>'
              br
              = '  </fieldset>'
              br
              = '</form>'

        h6 Example
        .example
          form
            fieldset
              legend Legend
              label
                | Input label
                input type="text" placeholder="Input placeholder..."

      section
        h3 Labels
        p 
          | You can show labels as inline or as block (default). To display the labels as inline you can put the label inside a different column to the left of the input. If you like the label to have an align to the right add a class of 
          code .label-right 
          | to the label. You can easily adjust the formatting of the labels by changing the following variables in 
          code config/_forms.scss
          | :
        p
          code $color-label
          | Font color for the label. (default: $color-black)
        p
          code $font-size-label
          | Fontsize for the label. (default: $font-size-default)
        p
          code $line-height-label
          | Lineheight for the label. (default: $line-height-default)
        h6 Usage
