        h3 Post- and prefixes f√ºr labels and actions
        p 
          | With muffins default-theme you can use some post-prefixes to explain your fields. You can easily adjust them by changing the following variables in 
          code config/_forms.scss
          | :
        p
          code $color-background-postprefix
          | Background color for post- and prefixes. (default: $color-gray-lighter)
        p
          code $color-postfix 
          | Font color for post- und prefixes. (default: $color-gray)
        p
          code $color-border-post-prefix
          | Border color for post- und prefixes. (default: $color-gray)
        p 
          | You have to add the class
          code .collapse
          |  to you "row"-div to prevent the paddings for the grid. Otherwise you will have space between the pre- or postfix und and the label. You can use pre- or postfix as single or together. Easily create a span with the class
          code .prefix
          |  or 
          code .postfix
          |  .
        h6 Usage
        pre
          code
            header HTML
            p
              = '<div class="row collapse">'
              br
              = '  <label>Input with prefix </label>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-2">'
              br
              = '    <span class="prefix"> http:// </span>'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-10">'
              br
              = '    <input type"text" placeholder="Input..." />'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '</div>'
              br
              = '<div class="row collapse">'
              br
              = '  <label>Input with postfix </label>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-10">'
              br
              = '    <input type"text" placeholder="Input..." />'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-2">'
              br
              = '    <span class="postfix"> .com </span>'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '</div>'
              br
              = '<div class="row collapse">'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-2">'
              br
              = '    <span class="prefix"> http:// </span>'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '  <label>Input with prefix and postfix </label>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-8">'
              br
              = '    <input type"text" placeholder="Input..." />'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '  <div class="col-xs-2">'
              br
              = '    <span class="postfix"> .com </span>'
              br
              = '  </div>'
              br
              = '</div>'
        h6 Example
        .example
          .row.collapse
            label Input with prefix
            .col-xs-2
              span.prefix http://
            .col-xs-10
              input type="text" placeholder="Input.."
          .row.collapse
            label Input with postfix
            .col-xs-10
              input type="text" placeholder="Input.."
            .col-xs-2
              span.postfix .com
          .row.collapse
            label Input with prefix and postfix
            .col-xs-2
              span.prefix http://
            .col-xs-8
              input type="text" placeholder="Input.."
            .col-xs-2
